{{Infobox prepared food | name = Bob chorba | image = Bean soup with tomatoes and red peppers.jpeg | caption = Bulgarian bean soup with tomatoes and red peppers | alternate_name = | country = [[Bulgaria]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Soup]] | served = | main_ingredient = Dried [[bean]]s, [[onion]]s, [[tomato]]es, [[Summer savory|chubritza]] or dzhodzhen ([[spearmint]]), [[carrot]]s | variations = Bean soup with sausage(which is like the normal bean soup, but with added sausage in it). | calories = | other = }}
'''Bob chorba''' ({{lang-bg|[[:bg:Боб чорба|боб чорба]]}}) is a [[chorba]], a national [[Bulgaria]]n dish. The name translates to "bean soup".<ref name="Kinser 2014">{{cite book | last=Kinser | first=K. | title=Vegan Beans from Around the World: 100 Adventurous Recipes for the Most Delicious, Nutritious, and Flavorful Bean Dishes Ever | publisher=Ulysses Press | year=2014 | isbn=978-1-61243-285-4 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qitfAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA29 | access-date=November 6, 2018 | page=29}}</ref> It is a soup made from dry [[bean]]s, [[onion]]s, [[tomato]]es, [[Summer savory|chubritza]] or dzhodzhen ([[spearmint]]) and [[carrot]]s.<ref name="Kinser 2014"/><ref name="Albala 2011"/>
Local variations may also exclude the carrots or include [[paprika]], [[potato]]es or even some kind of meat. Historically, it has been a common soup and [[staple food]] at Bulgarian monasteries.<ref name="Albala 2011">{{cite book | last=Albala | first=K. | title=Food Cultures of the World Encyclopedia | publisher=Greenwood | series=Food Cultures of the World Encyclopedia | issue=v. 2 | year=2011 | isbn=978-0-313-37626-9 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NTo6c_PJWRgC&pg=RA3-PA67 | access-date=November 6, 2018 | page=67}}</ref>
