==Overview== The '''Dynacord ADD-One''' (Advanced Digital Drums) is a german [[Drum Machine]] that was first released in 1986. It uses samples to produce its sounds. It comes with 1Mbyte of memory and can be upgraded up to 8Mbs.
==Sample Rate== The unit can sample at 50 khz at 12-bits <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicgeardaily.com/dynacord-add-one-rare-drum-machine/|title=Dynacord ADD-one rare drum machine {{!}} Music Gear Daily|website=www.musicgeardaily.com|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> for up to 20 seconds.
==Display== The unit featues a 80-character backlit [[LCD]].
==Sounds== Bass drums, congas, snares and Hihats.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dreamsong.de/vintage-drums-dynacord-add-one|title=Vintage Drums: Dynacord ADD-One|date=2011-02-27|work=Kreativ Musik machen|access-date=2018-06-05|language=de-DE}}</ref>
==External Control== The Chain mode allows these to be called up in any order and stepped through by a footswitch. The unit also features [[MIDI]] which allows it to be controlled from an external deivce such as a [[synthesizer]] or [[electronic drums]].
==Notable users== [[Jean-Michel Jarre]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jarrography.free.fr/details_equipement_audio.php?id_equip=81|title=DYNACORD ADD-One|website=www.jarrography.free.fr|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>
