{{Infobox military award |name = Order of the National Hero |image = |caption = |awarded_by = {{flagicon|Belize}} [[Belize]] |type = [[Order (decoration)|Order]] |motto = |day = |eligibility = Belizean citizens |for = "Extraordinary and outstanding achievement and merit in service to Belize or to humanity at large." |status = Currently constituted |commander = |grades = |former_grades = |established = 16 August 1991 |first_award = 2000 |last_award = 2009 |total = 3 |recipients = |individual = |higher = ''None'' |lower = [[Order of Belize]] |image2 = |caption2 = }}
The '''Order of the National Hero''' is the highest [[Commonwealth realms orders and decorations|honour]] awarded by the government of [[Belize]]. The Order of the National Hero is given for "extraordinary and outstanding achievement and merit in service to Belize or to humanity at large." Unlike the lower [[Order of Belize]] which can be awarded to foreign dignitaries, only Belizean citizens are eligible for the Order of the National Hero.
The order was instituted on 16 August 1991. As of 2014 the Order of the National Hero has been awarded three times, twice posthumously.<ref name="caribbean">[http://www.caribbeanelections.com/knowledge/biography/heroes/bz_heroes.asp National Heroes of Belize], Caribbean Elections. (accessed 24 October 2014)</ref>
==Recipients==
*[[George Cadle Price]], 2000 *[[Philip Goldson]] (posthumous), 2008<ref name="goldson">[http://www.7newsbelize.com/sstory.php?nid=12105 "Phillip Goldson Will BE Named National Hero"], [[Tropical Vision Limited]], September 3, 2008. (accessed 24 October 2014)</ref> *[[Monrad Metzgen]] (posthumous), 2009
